'''Rush Poppers'''，又可简称'''芳香剂'''、'''Rush'''或'''Poppers'''，是各种[[亚硝酸酯|亚硝酸酯]]——特别是[[亞硝酸異丙酯|亞硝酸異丙酯]]（2-propyl nitrite）、亚硝酸异丁酯（2-methylpropyl nitrite）以及较为罕见的[[亞硝酸正丁酯|亚硝酸丁酯]]（butyl nitrite）和[[亞硝酸异戊酯|亞硝酸异戊酯]]（isopentyl nitrite）——的[[俚语|代称]]。<ref name="TheSite">{{cite web|title=Poppers: The effects, the risks, the law|url=http://www.thesite.org/drinkanddrugs/drugsafety/drugsatoz/poppers|accessdate=2007-03-14|work=[[TheSite.org|TheSite.org]]|publisher=YouthNet UK|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070314225450/http://www.thesite.org/drinkanddrugs/drugsafety/drugsatoz/poppers|archivedate=2007-03-14|dead-url=yes}}</ref>亚硝酸异戊酯在医学上常用作氰化物中毒的[[解毒剂|解毒剂]]，<ref name="Medsafe">{{cite web|title=Amyl Nitrite|url=http://www.medsafe.govt.nz/Profs/datasheet/a/Amylnitrateinh.htm|accessdate=2007-03-15|date=2000-05-18|work=Medsafe|publisher=New Zealand Medicines and Medical Devices Safety Authority|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061111105814/http://www.medsafe.govt.nz/Profs/datasheet/a/Amylnitrateinh.htm|archivedate=2006-11-11|dead-url=yes}}</ref>但是“Poppers”一词仅限于指代其作为[[娛樂性用藥|娱乐性药物]]，中文译为'''情欲芳香剂'''，简称'''芳香剂'''。亚硝酸异戊酯及其他数种亚硝酸酯常见于空气清新剂、磁头清洁剂<ref name="Inhalants">{{cite web|title=Inhalants|url=http://www.dsamh.utah.gov/inhalants.htm |access-date=2011-09-12 |work=This text came from NIDA (National Institute on Drug Abuse)|publisher=Utah Department of Human Services|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110819203331/http://www.dsamh.utah.gov/inhalants.htm|archivedate=2011-08-19|dead-url=yes}}</ref>及指甲油去除剂中，<ref>{{cite web|title=What are Poppers?|url=http://www.4poppers.com/what-are-poppers.php|accessdate=2012-12-25|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130312003216/http://www.4poppers.com/what-are-poppers.php|archivedate=2013-03-12|dead-url=yes}}</ref>因此也常会被用于提高性快感。<ref name="Merck">{{cite encyclopedia|url=http://www.merck.com/mmpe/sec15/ch198/ch198m.html#sec15-ch198-ch198m-400|title=Volatile Nitrites|accessdate=2007-03-16|encyclopedia=[[The_Merck_Manual_Online|The Merck Manual Online]]|publisher=[[默克藥廠|Merck & Co.]]|editor=Porter, Robert S., et al.|date=November 2005|archivedate=2007-05-09|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070509220150/http://www.merck.com/mmpe/sec15/ch198/ch198m.html#sec15-ch198-ch198m-400|dead-url=no}}</ref>这些产品自20世纪70年代起成为了一种俱乐部文化。<ref name="Drugscope">{{cite web|title=Nitrites|url=http://www.drugscope.org.uk/druginfo/drugsearch/ds_results.asp?file=%5Cwip%5C11%5C1%5C1%5Cnitrites.html|accessdate=2007-04-24|work=Drugscope|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070405132026/http://www.drugscope.org.uk/druginfo/drugsearch/ds_results.asp?file=%5Cwip%5C11%5C1%5C1%5Cnitrites.html|archivedate=2007-04-05|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

尽管至少有一份分析指出，Poppers对于社会和个体的危害风险相比其他[[毒品|娱乐性药物]]所带来的风险要小，但是有其他的案例表明其可能导致严重的副作用。一份在《[[新英格兰医学杂志|新英格兰医学杂志]]》发表的信件表示，一位眼科医师记录了四例因使用Poppers导致视力发生临时性变化的案例。<ref>{{Cite news|title=Vision: A Quick High for Sex May Damage Vision|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/19/health/research/19vision.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2010-10-18|accessdate=2020-06-15|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Roni Caryn|last=Rabin|archivedate=2020-08-24|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200824170425/https://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/19/health/research/19vision.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>有些证据表明即便是偶尔使用也可能会影响视力。<ref name="vision">{{Cite web|title=Club drug 'poppers' may be linked to eye damage - USATODAY.com|url=https://usatoday30.usatoday.com/yourlife/health/medical/2010-10-16-drugs-poppers_N.htm|accessdate=2020-06-15|work=usatoday30.usatoday.com|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160120094353/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/yourlife/health/medical/2010-10-16-drugs-poppers_N.htm|archivedate=2016-01-20|dead-url=no}}</ref>

意外吞咽Popper瓶中之液体（而不是吸入液体的挥发物）是相当危险的，并且可能会致命。<ref name="Dixon-1981">{{Cite journal|title=Fatal methemoglobinemia resulting from ingestion of isobutyl nitrite, a "room odorizer" widely used for recreational purposes|url=https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/7252472|last=Dixon|first=D. S.|last2=Reisch|first2=R. F.|date=1981-07|journal=Journal of Forensic Sciences|issue=3|volume=26|pages=587–593|issn=0022-1198|pmid=7252472|last3=Santinga|first3=P. H.|access-date=2021-03-26|archive-date=2022-01-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220121070638/https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/7252472/}}</ref><ref name="Hagan-">{{Cite journal|title=Radiology of Recreational Drug Abuse|url=https://pubs.rsna.org/doi/full/10.1148/rg.274065103|last=Hagan|first=Ian G.|last2=Burney|first2=Kashif|date=2007-07-01|journal=RadioGraphics|issue=4|doi=10.1148/rg.274065103|volume=27|pages=919–940|issn=0271-5333|pmid=17620459|access-date=2021-03-26|archive-date=2019-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403050513/https://pubs.rsna.org/doi/full/10.1148/rg.274065103}}</ref>

